sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as Client App /<br/>Generated Axios SDK
    participant Core as cactus-cmd-api-server<br/>(core + PluginRegistry)
    participant Plugin as Ledger Connector Plugin<br/>(IPluginLedgerConnector)
    participant KC as Keychain Plugin<br/>(IPluginKeychain)
    participant BC as Blockchain Network

    Note over Core: Boot time — PluginRegistry imports each plugin,<br/>calls registerWebServices() and mounts OpenAPI routes
    App->>Core: POST /api/v1/plugins/.../run-transaction<br/>(OpenAPI request)
    activate Core
    Core->>Plugin: dispatch to endpoint handler
    activate Plugin
    Plugin->>KC: get signing credential
    activate KC
    KC-->>Plugin: private key (held only for signing)
    deactivate KC
    Plugin->>BC: JSON-RPC / gRPC / native SDK call
    activate BC
    BC-->>Plugin: transaction receipt
    deactivate BC
    Plugin-->>Core: typed RunTransactionResponse
    deactivate Plugin
    Core-->>App: JSON response (200)
    deactivate Core
    Note over App,BC: The core never talks to a ledger directly —<br/>every ledger interaction flows through a plugin + connector.
